# Spring Boot Ultimate Production Rules - Null Safety (10 Rules)

1. Never return `null` from service or repository contracts where alternatives exist.
2. Use `Optional<T>` for absent single-value lookup results at repository/service boundaries.
3. Validate all external input (`@Valid`, `@NotNull`, `@NotBlank`, range checks) before business logic.
4. Fail fast with explicit exceptions on invalid state instead of propagating nulls.
5. Initialize collections to empty collections, not null references.
6. Prefer constructor injection and `final` fields to avoid partially initialized objects.
7. Guard all nullable integration responses before mapping into domain objects.
8. Avoid chained dereferencing without guards; use explicit checks or mapping helpers.
9. Enforce non-null contracts in DTOs and domain constructors.
10. Ban `Optional.get()` without prior presence checks; use `orElseThrow`.
